FBIS3-653 "drafr048_c_94016" FBIS-AFR-94-048 Document Type:Daily Report 11 Mar 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Violence Descends on Bophuthatswana as Government Flees Rietgat Police Station Attacked MB1103101894 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1006 GMT 11 Mar 94 MB1103101894 Johannesburg SAPA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Report by N. Patterton] [Excerpt] Pretoria March 11 SAPA -- Rietgat police station was attacked with a petrol-bomb on Friday [11 March] as violence continued in areas of Bophuhatswana north-west of Pretoria. Rietgat, however, is on South African territory between Mabopane and Hammanskraal. Gunfire had been exchanged with the South African police, residents said. Bophuthatswana areas north-west of Pretoria such as Winterveld, Mabopane and Garankuwa were torn by violence, looting and shooting on Thursday night and Friday morning, according to witnesses. [passage omitted]
